<TITLE> Company driver killed by 'muggers' in capital </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 6 (bdnews24.com)  A driver of Opsonin Pharma Ltd was killed in front of the company's office at New Eskaton in the capital early Saturday, police said. The dead man was identified as Aminul Islam, 25. Ramna police chief Shibli Noman told bdnews24.com that they primarily suspected muggers might have stabbed him. "We are investigating whether there are any other reasons behind the murder," he said. Opsonin employee Nayeb Ali said Aminul was on board a pickup at around 3:45am in front of the 30 New Eskatan Road office. Some three to four muggers were trying to hijack the pickup. As Aminul confronted them, the muggers stabbed him and fled the scene, said Nayeb. Aminul was taken to Dhaka Medical College Hospital where he was declared dead, he said. bdnew
